description: From Middle English strengthful, strenkyþfull, equivalent to strength +‎ -ful.

adjectives.description: strengthful (comparative more strengthful, superlative most strengthful)

entries.meaning: (archaic) Full of strength; strong; having strength; powerful.
examples: I couldn't bring myself to say 'No, Ethelinda, I can not be yours because my heart is set on a strengthful damsel with raven locks and eyes of coal, with lips a shade less cherry than thine, and a cheek more like the apple than the peach, [...]'
